## 2) Add an “About” link → modal showing README.md + extra info

### UX requirements
- Add a link/button in the top navigation/header: **“About”**.
- Clicking opens a modal with:
  - Rendered README content (markdown → HTML).
  - Project metadata (version, links).
  - Attribution: **Author: Matthew Felsted**.

### Implementation options
1) **Build-time import** README (best for SPA builds):
   - Vite/Webpack can import raw markdown.
2) **Fetch at runtime** from `/README.md` (works if served):
   - `fetch('/README.md')` then render.

### Markdown rendering
Use a markdown renderer appropriate to your stack:
- JS: `marked`, `markdown-it`, `remark`.
- React: `react-markdown`.

### Minimal plain-HTML example (About modal)
**Modal markup:**
```html
<dialog id="aboutDialog">
  <div style="max-width: 900px;">
    <h2>About</h2>
    <p><strong>Author:</strong> Matthew Felsted</p>

    <div id="readmeContainer" class="markdown-body"></div>

    <hr />
    <p>
      <a href="https://github.com/<YOUR_ORG_OR_USER>/codex_manager" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Repository</a>
    </p>

    <menu style="display:flex; justify-content:flex-end;">
      <button id="closeAboutBtn">Close</button>
    </menu>
  </div>
</dialog>
```

**JS wiring (fetch README + render):**
```js
import { marked } from 'marked';

const aboutLink = document.getElementById('aboutLink');
const aboutDialog = document.getElementById('aboutDialog');
const closeAboutBtn = document.getElementById('closeAboutBtn');
const readmeContainer = document.getElementById('readmeContainer');

let readmeLoaded = false;

aboutLink.addEventListener('click', async (e) => {
  e.preventDefault();

  if (!readmeLoaded) {
    const res = await fetch('/README.md');
    const md = await res.text();
    readmeContainer.innerHTML = marked.parse(md);
    readmeLoaded = true;
  }

  aboutDialog.showModal();
});

closeAboutBtn.addEventListener('click', () => aboutDialog.close());
```

### “Whatever else you think should go there” (suggested About content)
Add a small section above/below the README:
- Purpose/one-liner description
- Supported providers list
- Privacy note about API keys
- Version/build info (commit hash if available)
- Links: Issues, Docs, License

---

## 3) Styling and accessibility checklist
- Use semantic buttons for actions; links for navigation.
- Ensure modals:
  - Trap focus (native `<dialog>` does this reasonably; otherwise implement focus trap).
  - Close on ESC
